Inflammation in atherosclerosis: a cause or a result of vascular disorders?.




			


		The platelet glycoprotein Ibα (GPIbα) and P-selectin glycoprotein ligand (PSGL-1) receptors bind to the endothelial P-selectin initiating platelet rolling, whereas the subsequent firm adhesion is mediated through αIIbβ3 integrin and P-selectin.
	